Description: Bronze figure of serpent-headed deity wearing atef-crown, left forearm raised, right fist clenched, with holes through hands for insertion of emblems, now lost; incised markings on crown, tripartite wig, kilt, and serpent head and neck.
Curator's comments: Similar figures, without atef-crown, can be identified as Heneb, cf. Limme, BMRAH 59 (1988): 23-4 [5]
